Description: debugging symbols for stone-base
 Stone is a massively scalable, open-source, distributed
 storage system that runs on commodity hardware and delivers object,
 block and file system storage.
 .
 This package contains the libraries and management tools that are common among
 the Stone server daemons (stone-mon, stone-mgr, stone-osd, stone-mds). These tools
 are necessary for creating, running, and administering a Stone storage cluster.
 .
 This package contains the debugging symbols for stone-base.

Package: stoneadm
Architecture: linux-any
Recommends: podman (>= 2.0.2) | docker.io
Depends: lvm2,
	 ${python:Depends},
Description: stoneadm utility to bootstrap stone daemons with systemd and containers
 Stone is a massively scalable, open-source, distributed
 storage system that runs on commodity hardware and delivers object,
 block and file system storage.
 .
 The stoneadm utility is used to bootstrap a Stone cluster and to manage
 stone daemons deployed with systemd and containers.

